ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-1 The captain/check airman reported that the accident flight was the first officer's second Initial Operating Experience (IOE) training flight after being hired by the airline. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-4 The captain said that at this point, he closed the throttles and instructed the first officer to maintain attitude as the second touchdown approached. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-8 A subsequent inspection by ground personnel discovered a 1 foot by 4 feet scrape located on the belly of the airplane, between station 887 and 941. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-7 After landing rollout, the airplane was taxied to the gate, and all of the 140 passengers disembarked the airplane uneventfully. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-2 He stated that the first officer was making a visual approach to runway 26, and on initial touchdown the airplane 'skipped' and became airborne. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-5 He said that the auto spoilers then deployed, and the airplane settled onto the runway in a nose high attitude. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-6 The captain characterized the second touchdown as 'firm', but well within acceptable limits. 
ntsb3549txt-1-5-5-0-3 The captain stated that during the initial touchdown he noted that the throttles were not in the fully retarded position. 
